  "excludedLineIds": [],
  "lineCount": 139,
  "lines": [
    {
      "lineNumber": 1,
      "text": "U.S. News & World Report",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 2,
      "text": "WASHINGTON, D. C.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 3,
      "text": "VOLUME XXXVIII—No. 14",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 4,
      "text": "FLYING SAUCERS—THE REAL STORY:",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "text": "U.S. BUILT FIRST ONE IN 1942",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "text": "Jet-Propelled Disks Can Outfly Other Planes",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "text": "Observers of \"flying saucers\"",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "text": "aren't just seeing things. They're",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "real—aircraft that conform to ac-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "cepted laws.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "Sky disks, manned by human",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "pilots, can hover aloft, leap",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "ahead at tremendous speed, out-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "text": "maneuver conventional craft.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "No official announcements are",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "being made yet. But about the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "only big secret left is Who makes",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "them. Evidence points to Navy",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "experiments.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "The real story on flying saucers",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "is finally coming to light. What",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "saucers are, how they operate, and",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "how they have been tested in flight",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "—all can be told in detail at this",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "time.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "That story, without violating",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "security regulations, points to these",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "conclusions by engineers competent",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "to appraise reports of reliable observers:",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "Flying saucers, \"seen\" by hundreds",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "of competent observers over most",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "parts of U. S., are accepted as real.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "Evidence is that they are aircraft of a",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "text": "revolutionary type, a combination",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "of helicopter and fast jet plane.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "They conform to well-known prin-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "ciples of aerodynamics. An early",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "model of these saucers was built by",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "U. S. engineers in 1942, and achieved",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "text": "more than 100 successful test flights.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "text": "That project then was taken over by",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 42,
      "text": "the Navy in wartime. Much more",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 43,
      "text": "advanced models now are being",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 44,
      "text": "built. This is where present saucers",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 45,
      "text": "come in. The story, pieced together",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 46,
      "text": "from unclassified testimony of many",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 47,
      "text": "responsible U. S. scientists, ob-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 48,
      "text": "servers and military officials, is this:",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 49,
      "text": "Early models of the flying",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 50,
      "text": "saucer pictured on this page and",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 51,
      "text": "described below were built by U. S.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 52,
      "text": "Government engineers of the National",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 53,
      "text": "Advisory Committee for Aeronautics",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 54,
      "text": "(NACA).",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 55,
      "text": "Similar flying-saucer projects were",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 56,
      "text": "begun in Germany and Italy at the same",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 57,
      "text": "time, in 1942.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 58,
      "text": "The first U. S. model, designed by",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 59,
      "text": "Charles H. Zimmerman, of NACA, was",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 60,
      "text": "elliptical in shape, powered by two piston",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 61,
      "text": "engines and driven by twin propellers.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 62,
      "text": "It had a maximum speed between 400",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 63,
      "text": "and 500 miles an hour. More important,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 64,
      "text": "it could rise almost vertically and its",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 65,
      "text": "minimum speed for landing was only",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 66,
      "text": "about 35 miles an hour, a great advan-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 67,
      "text": "tage in military and naval aircraft. And it",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 68,
      "text": "was far more maneuverable than con-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 69,
      "text": "ventional military planes.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 70,
      "text": "Idea behind those original flying-sau-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 71,
      "text": "cer projects, both in U. S. and abroad in",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 72,
      "text": "Germany and Italy, was to overcome",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 73,
      "text": "basic drawbacks of conventional aircraft",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 74,
      "text": "by new techniques. A plane that could",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 75,
      "text": "rise almost straight would not need long",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 76,
      "text": "runways, and airfields could be used from",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 77,
      "text": "any cleared area just behind front-line",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 78,
      "text": "troops or from the deck of any Navy",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 79,
      "text": "combat ship. If that plane, in addition,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 80,
      "text": "had great speed and more maneuverability,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 81,
      "text": "it could probably outfly any conventional",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 82,
      "text": "aircraft. In United States, the first model",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 83,
      "text": "seemed to fulfill these requirements, but",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 84,
      "text": "the lessened stability of the wingless craft",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 85,
      "text": "required more research.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 86,
      "text": "Present flying saucers apparently",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 87,
      "text": "have overcome this problem of stability",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 88,
      "text": "by use of very advanced design. An",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 89,
      "text": "analysis of reports submitted by compe-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 90,
      "text": "tent observers show this:",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 91,
      "text": "What they look like, first, is de-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 92,
      "text": "scribed in well-documented accounts.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 93,
      "text": "Those accounts show saucers to be exact-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 94,
      "text": "ly 105 feet in diameter, circular in shape.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 95,
      "text": "They have what appear to be jet nozzles",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 96,
      "text": "arranged all around the outer rim, just",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 97,
      "text": "below the center of gravity. They are",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 98,
      "text": "made of a metal alloy, with a dull whitish",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 99,
      "text": "color. There are no rudders, ailerons, or",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 100,
      "text": "other protruding surfaces. From the side",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 101,
      "text": "the saucers appear about 10 feet thick.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 102,
      "text": "There are no exact measurements from",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 103,
      "text": "this angle in publicly available accounts.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 104,
      "text": "They are built in three layers, with the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 105,
      "text": "center layer slightly larger in diameter",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 106,
      "text": "than the other two.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 107,
      "text": "That is the picture agreed on by quali-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 108,
      "text": "fied observers of saucers in flight—com-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 109,
      "text": "mercial aircraft pilots, fighter pilots who",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 110,
      "text": "have chased these aircraft, trained air-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 111,
      "text": "plane spotters, high-ranking Army and",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 112,
      "text": "Air Force officers. It is backed by exact",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 113,
      "text": "measurement made by a group of",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 114,
      "text": "scientists last April near White",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 115,
      "text": "Sands Proving Ground base, with",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 116,
      "text": "instruments set up to observe high-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 117,
      "text": "altitude balloons, who suddenly ob-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 118,
      "text": "served a saucer and tracked it for",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 119,
      "text": "several minutes, thereby getting",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 120,
      "text": "reliable data on its size, speed, alti-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 121,
      "text": "tude and maneuverability.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 122,
      "text": "How they operate now can be",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 123,
      "text": "told in some detail, too. Based on",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 124,
      "text": "this description, the probable tech-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 125,
      "text": "nique used by current saucers is",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 126,
      "text": "explained by a top-level Govern-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 127,
      "text": "ment aeronautical engineer in this",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 128,
      "text": "manner:",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 129,
      "text": "Power for these aircraft, at their",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 130,
      "text": "present stage of development, ob-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 131,
      "text": "viously is supplied by jet engines.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 132,
      "text": "Each saucer appears to have a",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 133,
      "text": "series of variable-direction jet noz-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 134,
      "text": "zles around its rim, with a compli-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 135,
      "text": "cated central control system. Fuel",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 136,
      "text": "used is unknown—the exhaust flame",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 137,
      "text": "has been observed to be red-orange",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 138,
      "text": "in some cases, blue in others.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 139,
      "text": "NACA SAUCER 1942 MODEL",
      "status": "image_matched"
    }
  ],
  "blockCount": null
}
